A nostalgic vintage-style illustration of a child's hands assembling a classic electronics hobby kit on a worn wooden workbench, surrounded by colorful wires, small motors, batteries, and circuit components scattered artfully across the surface. Warm afternoon light streams through a nearby window, casting golden rays across the workspace. In the background, shelves display old vacuum tubes, magnets, and mechanical gears. The color palette features warm browns, brass tones, and pops of red and blue wiring. The scene evokes 1950s educational toy advertisements with slightly desaturated, dreamy quality and subtle grain texture.
